s://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go up, to ascend, to rise","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"صَعَدَ وَهَبَطَ","english":"to rise and fall"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mount, to ascend, to climb","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to climb aboard","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lead, to make ascend","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ascend, to climb, to mount"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause (someone/something) to rise or go up, to send (someone/something) up","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause","examples":[{"text":"صَعَّدَهُ جَبَلًا","english":"He made him climb a mountain"},{"text":"يُصَعِّدُونَهَا فِي الْجَبَلِ","english":"They make them (e.g. cows) climb the mountain"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to melt (fat, etc.)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sublimate (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to (cause to) evaporate, to vaporize (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to expand, to grow (something)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to utter (a sigh, a wail, a groan, etc.)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw (breath)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"top, the top part"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَعِدَ (ṣaʕida, “to go up, ascend”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"going up, ascending"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mounting, climbing"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"terrible punishment, pain, torture"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَعِدَ (ṣaʕida, “to go up, ascend”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"going up, ascending"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mounting, climbing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"high"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew צַעַד (tsaʿad)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24308","headword_ar":"صعّد","root":"SEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoEiydN","text_ar":"تَصْعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as intrans.: see above, in four places. ―         -b2-  And see also 4, in four places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SE~dhu","text_ar":"صعّدهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him, to ascend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mount;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aAhu","text_ar":"عَلَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raq~aAhu","text_ar":"رَقَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqY","text_ar":"رقى"},{"kind":"text","text":";) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASEdhu","text_ar":"اصعدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstSEdhu","text_ar":"استصعدهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as one says in the contr. sense"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naz~alahu","text_ar":"نَزَّلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anozalahu","text_ar":"اَنْزَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotanozalahu","text_ar":"اِسْتَنْزَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SE~dhu jabalFA","text_ar":"صعّدهُ جَبَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~apN","text_ar":"دَابَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to ascend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mount, a mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aljabali","text_ar":"فِى الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuSoEiduwnahaA","text_ar":"يُصْعِدُونَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said with reference to wild bulls or cows [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They make them to ascend upon the mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"slE","text_ar":"سلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaE~ada fiY~a Aln~aZara","text_ar":"صَعَّدَ فِىَّ النَّظَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSaw~abahu","text_ar":"وَصَوَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked at me from head to foot, contemplating me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, from a trad. [And a similar phrase occurs in Har p. 640.]) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SE~dhu","text_ar":"صعّدهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoEiydN","text_ar":"تَصْعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (the latter as used in the K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfuwrN","text_ar":"كَافُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sublimated it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"often occurring in medical books, and used in this sense in the present day.] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoEiydN","text_ar":"تَصْعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liquifying, melting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissolving."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-  See also 4, last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24314","headword_ar":"صُعْدٌ","root":"SEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudN","text_ar":"صُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24315","headword_ar":"صَعَدٌ","root":"SEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEuwdN","text_ar":"صَعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAbN SaEadN","text_ar":"عَذَابٌ صَعَدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vehement, severe, rigorous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grievous, punishment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw SaEadK","text_ar":"ذُو صَعَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a distressing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an afflicting, punishment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in lxxii. 17,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that shall overcome the sufferer thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the latter word being an inf. n. used as an epithet. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n24316","headword_ar":"صُعُدٌ","root":"SEd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEida","text_ar":"صَعِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (Ham p. 407.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Als~ahomu SuEudFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ السَّهْمُ صُعُدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The arrow went upwards"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA Aln~abaAtu yanomiY SuEudFA","text_ar":"هٰذَا النَّبَاتُ يَنْمِى صُعُدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This plant increases in height."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaf~asa","text_ar":"تَنَفَّسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudFA","text_ar":"صُعُدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEadaA='u","text_ar":"صُعَدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino SuEodK","text_ar":"مِنْ صُعْدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used by poetic license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn SuEudK","text_ar":"من صُعُدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], said of a thing falling, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From above; from a higher place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 349.)       -A2-  Also a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEuwdN","text_ar":"صَعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEiydN","text_ar":"صَعِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEudN","text_ar":"صُعُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus, with two dammehs, is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree from which pitch is melted forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}